title: Gnarosophia bellendenkerensis
text:
Gnarosophia bellendenkerensis is a <a href="species">species</a> of air-breathing <a href="land%20snail">land snail</a>, a <a href="terrestrial%20animal">terrestrial</a> <a href="pulmonate">pulmonate</a> <a href="gastropod">gastropod</a> <a href="mollusk">mollusk</a> in the family <a href="Camaenidae">Camaenidae</a>.
Distribution.
This species lives in <a href="rainforest">rainforest</a>s in <a href="North%20Queensland">North Queensland</a>, Australia.
The type locality is <a href="Bellenden%20Ker%20Range">Bellenden Ker Mountains</a>, Queensland.
Description.
The height of the <a href="gastropod%20shell">shell</a> is 33.08 mm. The width of the shell is 40.19 mm.
Ecology.
These snails live in <a href="leaf%20litter">leaf litter</a> or under logs in the mesothermal rainforest.
